description:
A graphic biography of 1930s Hollywood Star Vivien Leigh.

Written and hand drawn by Jessica Martin.

Published by ArtyMiss Publishing.

'Elsie Harris Picture Palace' is Jessica Martin's debut graphic novel.

It was shortlisted for the Myriad First Graphic Novel Prize, 2015.

This hardback volume of over 150 pages continues in Jessica's distinct black and white film style with the tale of young Londoner Elsie who embarks on a journey taking her from Elstree to Hollywood in the 1930s.

Inspired by the unsung genius of the art creatives of the film industry, this is a unique spin on the rags to riches story in the glamorous world of film.

Romance, adventure and mystery await you at the Picture Palace!

description:
"El zoológico, las meriendas, los amigos, pasear con tus padres, la primera novia; delicias de la niñez… ¿o no?

Bubbles, (como Peanuts (Snoopy), Little Lulu, Nancy (Periquita), Mafalda o Calvin & Hobbes) es una historieta sobre la infancia. Pero no la infancia nostálgica edulcorada por el recuerdo; la inquietante infancia vivida por un niño: Bubbles.

Durante ese recorrido Bubbles se enfrentará al primer amor, a las siestas de verano, a los paseos, a la consciencia de muerte, al circo, a los juegos y toda experiencia que hoy, de lejos, nos parecen normales y sencillas, pero que vividas por primera vez son intensas y, muchas veces, aterradoras."--Publisher's website

Includes three complete stories:

Cruise to Romance

Here's Your Chance, Rosemary

Honeymoon Express

and three ongoing serials

Lucky Madge

The Innocents In Paris

Rose the Slave Girl

plus reprints of Millie the Model

description: The third issue is here, and it marks our first detour from the main Chris' storyline as we get to know another masked killer, the guy behind the creepy raven mask that you can see on the cover. The story is written as usual by Federico Chemello and Maurizio Furini, but this time the art is handled by Ludovica Ceregatti (pencils and inks) and Giorgia Lanza (colors), a perfect way to underline the change of perspective!

description: Our Mother is a comedy about growing up with a parent who has an anxiety order. Luke Howard mixes genres to tell an utterly open personal reflection about his childhood and his relationship with his mother. Jumping between noir, giant robots, fantasy adventure, and even scientific animal research, Luke brings a very intimate story to life with humor and cartooning experimentation.
